name: r-shinymodels
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-shinymodels
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/shinymodels_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/shinymodels/shinymodels_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f16c22e8bf0c9b81935648e5b4060559aac0a03828bbee5bf6dc9fb0f544ec9c

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dt
    - r-dplyr
    - r-generics >=0.1.0
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-glue
    - r-htmltools
    - r-magrittr
    - r-parsnip
    - r-plotly
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-scales
    - r-shiny
    - r-shinydashboard
    - r-tidyr
    - r-tidyselect
    - r-tune
    - r-yardstick
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dt
    - r-dplyr
    - r-generics >=0.1.0
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-glue
    - r-htmltools
    - r-magrittr
    - r-parsnip
    - r-plotly
    - r-purrr
    - r-rlang
    - r-scales
    - r-shiny
    - r-shinydashboard
    - r-tidyr
    - r-tidyselect
    - r-tune
    - r-yardstick

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('shinymodels')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('shinymodels')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://shinymodels.tidymodels.org, https://github.com/tidymodels/shinymodels
  license: MIT
  summary: Launch a 'shiny' application for 'tidymodels' results. For classification or regression
    models, the app can be used to determine if there is lack of fit or poorly predicted
    points.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
